2018–19 Italian Women's Volleyball Leagu:
The 2018–19 Serie A1 was the 74th season of the highest professional Italian Women's Volleyball League. The season took place from October to May and was contested by twelve teams.

The regular season consists of 24 rounds, where the twelve participating teams play each other twice (once home and once away). At the completion of the regular season, the seven best teams advance to the championship playoffs and the team finishing 12th is relegated to Serie A2. If the 12th team is Club Italia Crai, the team finishing 11th is relegated.

