2022–23 Italian Women's Volleyball Leagu:
The 2022–23 Serie A1 was the 79th season of the highest professional Italian Women's Volleyball League. The season took place from November to June and was contested by twelve teams.

The regular season consists of 24 rounds, where the twelve participating teams play each other twice (once home and once away). At the completion of the regular season, the six best teams advance to the championship playoffs, the 7-10th ranked teams advance to the challenge playoffs and the teams finishing 11th and 12th are relegated to Serie A2.

The standings criteria:
- highest number of result points (points awarded for results: 2 points for 3–0 or 3–1 wins, 1 point for 3–2 win, 0.5 points for 2–3 loss);
- highest number of matches won;
- highest set quotient (the number of total sets won minus the number of total sets lost);
- highest points quotient (the number of total points scored divided by the number of total points conceded).

2023–24 Italian Women's Volleyball Leagu:
The 2023–24 Serie A1 is the 79th season of the highest professional Italian Women's Volleyball League. The season takes place from September to March and is contested by twelve teams.

The regular season consists of 24 rounds, where the twelve participating teams play each other once (once home or away). At the completion of the regular season, the six best teams advance to the championship playoffs and the teams finishing 11th and 12th are relegated to Serie A2.

The standings criteria:

highest number of result points (points awarded for results: 2 points for 3–0 or 3–1 wins, 1 point for 3–2 win, 0 points for any loss);
highest number of matches won;
highest set quotient (the number of total sets won divided by the number of total sets lost);
highest points quotient (the number of total points scored divided by the number of total points conceded).

2023–24 Women's EHF European League Grou:
The 2023–24 EHF European League group stage was played between 6 January and 18 February 2024 to determine the four teams advancing to the knockout stage of the 2023–24 Women's EHF European League.


== Draw ==
The draw took place on the 23 November 2023 at 12:00 CET in Vienna, Austria. The only restriction was that clubs from the same country cannot be in the same group. Bold indicates who advanced to the knockout stage.


=== Seeding ===


== Format ==
In each group, teams played against each other in a single round-robin format, with home and away matches.


== Tiebreakers ==
In the group stage, teams were ranked according to goals scored (2 points for a win, 1 point for a draw, 0 points for a loss), and if tied on points, the following tiebreaking criteria were applied, in the order given, to determine the rankings:

Points in matches among tied teams;
Goal difference in all group matches;
Goals scored in all group matches;
If more than two teams were tied, and after applying all head-to-head criteria above, a subset of teams were still tied, all head-to-head criteria above were reapplied exclusively to this subset of teams;
Drawing lots.".
